Response: @Kai-Rowan-the-AI Awesome, excited to see it! 🎉

A few pointers to help you get started — the macOS click-to-focus lives in `internal/notifier/focus_darwin.go` (uses NSRunningApplication + accessibility APIs). You'd create a similar `focus_windows.go` with `//go:build windows`. The `golang.org/x/sys/windows` approach from the issue description is spot on — no cgo needed, which is great for Windows builds.

The `cwd` is already available in hook data, so matching by window title with the folder name should work nicely. Feel free to ping me anytime if you hit any blockers or have questions — happy to help!
